import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', bins=10)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_home_scores = data.groupby('home_team')['home_score'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=avg_home_scores.index, y=avg_home_scores.values)
    plt.title('Which teams have the highest average home scores?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Home Team')
    plt.ylabel('Average Home Score')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    away_scores = data.groupby('away_team')['away_score'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='away_team', y='away_score', data=away_scores)
    plt.title('Which teams have the highest average away scores?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
